# 40-ui: Admin UI Layout Rules

Applies to admin dashboards, CRUD forms, tables.

## Buttons
- Buttons must be width-by-content (default inline-flex).
- Use `w-auto` / do not use `w-full` on action buttons unless explicitly required.

## Input widths
- Short inputs (name, slug, email, phone, price, unit): max width **300px**.
- Long text/description fields: max width **650px**.

## Layout
- Use grid/flex with wrap so fields can sit side-by-side and wrap on small screens:
  - `grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2` or `flex flex-wrap gap-4`
- Button groups must use `flex flex-wrap gap-2`.

## FORBIDDEN
- ❌ Full-width action buttons by default.
- ❌ Forms where every short field spans the entire page width.
